1
00:01:39,010 --> 00:01:42,110
[Episode 7]

2
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,732
Alright, alright.

3
00:01:45,732 --> 00:01:47,715
I'll find a way.

4
00:01:49,879 --> 00:01:51,879
Smile.

5
00:01:51,879 --> 00:01:53,773
I can't.

6
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,457
I said I can't smile.

7
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,080
Grandma, slow down.

8
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:12,039
Have you seen Qing Ye?

9
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:13,400
She went to the beach.

10
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:16,435
She said she'd be back after a short walk.

11
00:02:21,159 --> 00:02:22,993
Grandma.

12
00:02:24,639 --> 00:02:28,260
Do you agree with my decision
to bring Qing Ye back?

13
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,199
Don't I know you?

14
00:02:32,199 --> 00:02:36,039
Even if it were a stray cat on the street,
You'd bring it back home.

15
00:02:36,039 --> 00:02:38,430
Let alone a person.

16
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:42,294
It's just hard on you.

17
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,360
As long as you're all doing well,

18
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,575
I don't mind it at all.

19
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,366
What're you looking at?

20
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,680
Zhazhating.

21
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,879
It feels...

22
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:18,392
both familiar and strange.

23
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,120
Last time you left,

24
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,525
you didn't plan on coming back, did you?

25
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:29,039
I thought if I left back then,

26
00:03:29,039 --> 00:03:31,703
everything would go back to how it was.

27
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:34,479
But actually,

28
00:03:34,479 --> 00:03:37,140
that world no longer belongs to me.

29
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,159
So when I came back this time,

30
00:03:40,159 --> 00:03:42,774
I was truly at a dead end.

31
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:46,120
I thought I'd be scared

32
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,480
and lost.

33
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:50,520
But instead, standing here,

34
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,879
I actually feel relieved.

35
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:55,400
It feels like my summer vacation

36
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,561
has finally begun.

37
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,719
That's a good attitude.

38
00:04:02,719 --> 00:04:03,840
Looks like

39
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,436
you've mostly sorted yourself out.

40
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:16,560
Xing Wu.

41
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,479
Thank you.

42
00:04:21,319 --> 00:04:23,205
For what?

43
00:04:24,279 --> 00:04:27,586
For giving me a chance to start over.

44
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:33,579
Don't mention it.

45
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:38,172
Have you seen those?

46
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,680
Hermit crabs?

47
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,079
Yeah.

48
00:04:46,079 --> 00:04:47,400
A hermit crab's life...

49
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,880
As it grows,

50
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,480
it constantly changes its shell.

51
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,594
Basically,

52
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:57,095
it keeps moving into new homes.

53
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,720
Every time it leaves its old shell,

54
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:03,122
that's when it's most vulnerable.

55
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:17,240
But as it gets used to the new shell,

56
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:22,085
it will eventually become tougher and stronger.

57
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:30,070
Same for people.

58
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:35,835
Auntie agreed to let me stay?

59
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,959
Since she accepted your gift,

60
00:05:37,959 --> 00:05:40,120
she has no reason to kick you out.

61
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,920
That's great.

62
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:45,439
I thought I'd be homeless again.

63
00:05:45,439 --> 00:05:47,680
No way.

64
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,920
You've got me.

65
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:52,757
I hope this year at Xuan Island,

66
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,800
you'll also become tougher

67
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,720
and stronger.

68
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,685
I will.

69
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,600
- Fang.
- You're back.

70
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,325
- The bill.
- Okay, come on.

71
00:06:25,325 --> 00:06:28,316
- Take it easy.
- Got it.

72
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:36,540
Fifty-eight.

73
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:40,661
[Sales Receipt]

74
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,879
That much?

75
00:06:46,879 --> 00:06:48,760
Still have debts to pay.

76
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,399
Fang, the gas tank is swapped.

77
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,400
Good. I'll WeChat you the money later.

78
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,320
Okay.

79
00:06:55,973 --> 00:06:57,199
Hey, you're here.

80
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,560
Auntie Liu.

81
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,279
Come, have a seat.

82
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:03,092
[Transfer to Liu Nian]
What style are we doing today?

83
00:07:03,092 --> 00:07:05,160
I've sent the money, Liu Nian.

84
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,986
Okay.

85
00:07:07,986 --> 00:07:09,986
[Debit card: Jul 23 online payment RMB 180.00,
balance RMB 511.39 (Lianhai Commercial Bank).]

86
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,360
Your hair...

87
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,575
I want a new look.

88
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,560
By the way,

89
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,199
from now on, this room

90
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:51,479
will be all yours.

91
00:07:51,479 --> 00:07:52,920
Then where will you stay?

92
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,145
The utility room downstairs.

93
00:07:54,145 --> 00:07:55,439
Is that room even livable?

94
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:57,000
Yes.

95
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,600
I usually crash at Shunyi anyway.

96
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,520
A bed is all I need.

97
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,720
Thanks.

98
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,030
Come on, you've said "thanks"
more than enough times today.

99
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,518
Wait a second.

100
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,007
This is for you.

101
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:27,319
I don't need this thing.

102
00:08:27,319 --> 00:08:29,040
Why not?

103
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:32,000
When you fix phones,
you're always hunching over.

104
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,639
It's bad for your neck.

105
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,460
Put it on.

106
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,559
Fine.

107
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,848
I'll wear it.

108
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:46,519
I know...

109
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:49,919
I'll be a big burden to you all from now on.

110
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:51,960
So I'll do my best

111
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,919
to help out as much as I can.

112
00:08:53,919 --> 00:08:56,320
I'll keep track of every single expense.

113
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,159
Once I start earning money,

114
00:08:58,159 --> 00:09:00,663
I'll pay you back with interest.

115
00:09:02,159 --> 00:09:03,480
Okay.

116
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,759
I'll be waiting for you

117
00:09:04,759 --> 00:09:05,960
to grow up

118
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,799
and take care of me.

119
00:09:07,799 --> 00:09:09,240
Take care of you?

120
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,707
Don't try to act like my elder.

121
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:16,159
Qing Ye,

122
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:18,871
stop seeing yourself as a burden.

123
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:21,480
You don't need to walk on eggshells

124
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,639
or worry about what we think.

125
00:09:22,639 --> 00:09:25,525
And stop thinking about debts and repayments.

126
00:09:26,159 --> 00:09:28,346
We treat you as family.

127
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:31,414
I hope you do the same.

128
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,345
Good night.

129
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,840
Mom,

130
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:58,679
it's still the same here,

131
00:10:58,679 --> 00:11:01,152
yet it's also very different.

132
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:38,000
Fruit! Selling fruit!

133
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,280
Fresh fruit!

134
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,399
Selling fruit!

135
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,879
Fruit! Fruit!

136
00:11:44,879 --> 00:11:48,120
Tofu for sale!

137
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,759
Fresh fruit!

138
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:53,754
Freshly made tofu!

139
00:11:54,799 --> 00:11:58,319
Tofu for sale!

140
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,552
Qin Ye, where are you? I'm worried about you.

141
00:12:05,552 --> 00:12:06,919
Don't overthink what my mom said.

142
00:12:06,919 --> 00:12:08,600
She didn't mean anything bad by it.

143
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:12,279
Just stay at my place with peace of mind.
Stay as long as you want.

144
00:12:12,279 --> 00:12:14,360
I promise to stand by my word.

145
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:17,519
Qing Ye, don't ignore me.

146
00:12:17,519 --> 00:12:19,600
I've returned to Zhazhating.

147
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,879
Zhazhating?

148
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:23,479
Didn't you hate that place?

149
00:12:25,039 --> 00:12:27,385
It's different now.

150
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,952
Alipay received 80 yuan.

151
00:12:38,952 --> 00:12:40,079
Li Lan Fang,

152
00:12:40,079 --> 00:12:41,799
didn't we agree on 85 yuan at least?

153
00:12:41,799 --> 00:12:43,799
Why did you round down the change?

154
00:12:43,799 --> 00:12:46,456
I only bought some conches,
scallops, and clams.

155
00:12:46,456 --> 00:12:47,593
80 yuan is enough.

156
00:12:47,593 --> 00:12:50,000
We don't make money easily. Up early, out late.

157
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,152
It's just five yuan, let it go.

158
00:12:51,152 --> 00:12:53,482
- Yeah, Yu.
- Right, we're old neighbors.

159
00:12:53,482 --> 00:12:55,639
- Regular customers.
- I'll buy from you next time, Yu.

160
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:57,840
- Fine, then. Come back often.
- Thanks, thanks.

161
00:12:57,840 --> 00:13:00,000
Thanks, Yu. We definitely will.

162
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,679
You're quite generous, buying so much.

163
00:13:02,679 --> 00:13:04,280
You were acting so high and mighty,

164
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:07,800
saying you didn't want her to come.

165
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,802
You've even put on the silk scarf.

166
00:13:09,802 --> 00:13:10,840
You're wearing it.

167
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,200
- It's really pretty.
- Looks good.

168
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,840
It must've been expensive.

169
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,400
Gifts soften the heart.

170
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,680
It'd be wrong to still be unhappy now.

171
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,720
It's not because of that.

172
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,320
Even though my family isn't well-off,

173
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,000
raising a child isn't like raising a fish.

174
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,960
I have to be responsible for her.

175
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,279
She's a young girl

176
00:13:26,279 --> 00:13:27,630
with a bright future ahead.

177
00:13:27,630 --> 00:13:31,080
If she's held back because of us,
how will I explain it to my sister?

178
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,440
That's true.

179
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:34,399
After all, she's someone else's child.

180
00:13:34,399 --> 00:13:36,360
You can't hit or scold her.

181
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,720
If she's even slightly unhappy,

182
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,080
you worry about upsetting her.
Like she's been wronged.

183
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,159
Exactly.

184
00:13:41,159 --> 00:13:44,639
Besides, I've never raised a girl before.

185
00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:47,159
Never raised a girl?
Weren't you once a girl yourself?

186
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:49,679
Didn't we all go through being 17 or 18?

187
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:52,240
Just follow the pattern.
Raise her like you were raised.

188
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,679
What's the problem?

189
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:56,039
Like I was raised? Oh, please.

190
00:13:56,039 --> 00:13:59,360
When I was seventeen or eighteen,
my life was a total mess.

191
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:03,475
I would never let Qing Ye live the way I did.

192
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:07,240
And you have the nerve to say I spend too much?

193
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:08,873
You, Xi Xi.

194
00:14:08,873 --> 00:14:10,159
I didn't!

195
00:14:10,159 --> 00:14:14,125
When you bought oysters for Hu's dad,
you were way more generous than me.

196
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,600
How much did you buy today?

197
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,440
Not much.

198
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,639
Xi Xi, you didn't buy enough today.

199
00:14:19,639 --> 00:14:21,320
How about we go with you

200
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:23,966
to buy some Mongolian onions, sea cucumbers,
and deer antler wine?

201
00:14:23,966 --> 00:14:25,000
Keep it down!

202
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,679
Aren't you ashamed with so many people
around? You two!

203
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,843
Sea cucumbers are over there.

204
00:14:28,843 --> 00:14:29,920
Deer antler wine too.

205
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:32,086
Look at her.

206
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,673
Bo!

207
00:14:36,673 --> 00:14:37,759
Your phone is fixed.

208
00:14:37,759 --> 00:14:39,690
Let me see.

209
00:14:41,639 --> 00:14:43,519
Not bad! You're good.

210
00:14:43,519 --> 00:14:45,240
How much for the repair?

211
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,360
- Free. Don't worry about it.
- No, no, no.

212
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,659
I'll transfer it to you on WeChat.

213
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:50,760
Thanks, Bo. I'm off.

214
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:52,229
Bye.

215
00:14:52,919 --> 00:14:54,679
Just round it down.

216
00:14:54,679 --> 00:14:55,960
430 yuan will do.

217
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,279
Okay.

218
00:14:57,279 --> 00:14:58,639
Sent via WeChat.

219
00:14:58,639 --> 00:15:00,579
Good.

220
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,903
Boss, I've paid.

221
00:15:08,903 --> 00:15:10,745
Alright.

222
00:15:12,347 --> 00:15:13,452
Bo.

223
00:15:13,452 --> 00:15:14,560
- Qing Ye.
- A bottle of water.

224
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:16,908
Sure, take it from here.

225
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,159
Same time today.

226
00:15:20,159 --> 00:15:22,639
Show up and you get paid.

227
00:15:22,639 --> 00:15:24,399
I've already taken several days off.

228
00:15:24,399 --> 00:15:26,320
They're already unhappy with me.

229
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:28,533
I really can't go anymore.

230
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:31,000
That shabby barbershop of yours...

231
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,913
How much can you even make there?

232
00:15:32,913 --> 00:15:34,559
Come with me to the city's karaoke bar.

233
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,840
You can make hundreds a day.

234
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,240
I don't want to quit.

235
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,440
Cutting hair with Fang is good.

236
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,621
It's really fine.

237
00:15:41,621 --> 00:15:42,640
Fine?

238
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:45,774
You can barely feed yourself.
What's so fine about it?

239
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:48,399
There are things you don't understand.

240
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:50,279
Fang's family is struggling now.

241
00:15:50,279 --> 00:15:52,292
I can't leave them now.

242
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:56,166
Fine, I can't win with you.

243
00:15:57,679 --> 00:16:00,159
Here's the money from yesterday.

244
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:02,945
Call me anytime if you change your mind.

245
00:16:22,799 --> 00:16:24,600
Hey, don't get me wrong.

246
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,440
I have no intention of leaving.

247
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:29,559
I think... your friend has a point.

248
00:16:29,559 --> 00:16:31,159
A city karaoke bar

249
00:16:31,159 --> 00:16:32,920
surely pays more than Xuan Island.

250
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,480
I won't leave no matter the pay.

251
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,720
I'm staying at Xuan Island

252
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,978
to repay a debt of gratitude.

253
00:16:40,057 --> 00:16:41,080
Gratitude?

254
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:43,503
Because Fang saved my life.

255
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,840
Six years ago,

256
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:51,960
if not for Fang and Wu...

257
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,840
I don't even know
where I'd be begging for food now.

258
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,440
After my parents divorced,

259
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,879
they each started new families.

260
00:16:58,879 --> 00:17:00,600
My grandma was old

261
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,739
and had to look after me alone.

262
00:17:02,739 --> 00:17:05,720
We were poor. I was malnourished as a kid,

263
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,960
so I've always been skinny.

264
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,884
Got bullied a lot.

265
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,880
During my vocational school years,
some punks picked on me.

266
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,107
What did you pick up?

267
00:17:15,107 --> 00:17:17,000
- Let's see.
- What are you doing?

268
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,839
You stinking beggar.

269
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:20,440
I-I'm not a beggar.

270
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,000
Say that again and I'll beat you up.

271
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,680
What are you doing?

272
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:27,179
Put that down and get lost.

273
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,986
Are you okay?

274
00:17:41,706 --> 00:17:42,920
I'm fine.

275
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,480
It was Wu

276
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,080
who brought me into Xuan Island.

277
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,920
That's three bowls already.

278
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:05,499
Wu, go to Bo's place and buy two more.

279
00:18:05,499 --> 00:18:07,880
- Okay.
- No need, no need.

280
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,400
I'm full.

281
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:12,646
Then eat slowly. Don't rush.

282
00:18:16,559 --> 00:18:19,160
How old are you?

283
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:21,480
18.

284
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:24,149
Even older than Wu.

285
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,799
Is there anyone else in your family?

286
00:18:27,799 --> 00:18:29,599
My family?

287
00:18:29,599 --> 00:18:31,673
Only my grandma is left.

288
00:18:42,319 --> 00:18:43,690
There.

289
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:46,240
Take a look. Much neater now.

290
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,209
Thank you, Auntie.

291
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,920
What happened after that?

292
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,440
After that,

293
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,524
Fang let me come to the shop

294
00:19:01,524 --> 00:19:02,839
to do odd jobs after school.

295
00:19:02,839 --> 00:19:03,880
Sweeping the floor.

296
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,440
She saw that I was hardworking.

297
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,720
So she asked me to stay
at the shop after graduation

298
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:09,039
and be her apprentice.

299
00:19:09,039 --> 00:19:11,100
I agreed right away.

300
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,825
Look.

301
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,200
That lone seagull

302
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,039
is just like me.

303
00:19:18,039 --> 00:19:19,400
Xuan Island

304
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,101
is like the nest that took me in.

305
00:19:21,759 --> 00:19:23,200
Fang and Wu

306
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,487
are my saviors.

307
00:19:25,487 --> 00:19:27,661
Hearing all that,

308
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,160
we're actually

309
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,120
quite similar.

310
00:19:32,812 --> 00:19:34,960
How could I be like you?

311
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:37,480
Since you were little,
you must have had a good life.

312
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:38,640
You don't understand.

313
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:40,160
When you're about to starve to death,

314
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,839
someone hands you a bowl of instant noodles.

315
00:19:42,839 --> 00:19:45,079
Or when you're swimming in the ocean

316
00:19:45,079 --> 00:19:46,240
and you're drowning,

317
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:48,559
someone tosses you a lifebuoy.

318
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:50,079
I understand.

319
00:19:50,079 --> 00:19:51,920
It's like

320
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:54,240
you're swimming desperately in the ocean,

321
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:56,799
but you can't reach the shore.

322
00:19:56,799 --> 00:19:59,745
Just when you're about to give up struggling,

323
00:20:00,559 --> 00:20:02,920
someone suddenly appears

324
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:05,119
and gives you a strong pull,

325
00:20:05,119 --> 00:20:07,519
bringing you back to life.

326
00:20:08,519 --> 00:20:10,925
You've had that experience too?

327
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:17,559
Xuan Island isn't just where I work.

328
00:20:17,559 --> 00:20:18,799
It's more like home

329
00:20:18,799 --> 00:20:20,660
than home itself.

330
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:28,559
About what happened just now,

331
00:20:28,559 --> 00:20:30,218
can you keep it a secret for me?

332
00:20:31,039 --> 00:20:32,160
Don't worry.

333
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:34,332
I have a seven-second memory.

334
00:20:34,332 --> 00:20:36,565
What did you just say?

335
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,299
Let's go. Otherwise, you'll be marked late.

336
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,640
Qing Ye!

337
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:50,440
Don't go in yet.

338
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,640
What's wrong?

339
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,227
The debt collectors are here.

340
00:20:54,227 --> 00:20:55,400
Don't go in yet!

341
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,346
I'll go take a look.

342
00:21:01,452 --> 00:21:02,565
Mr. Ma.

343
00:21:02,565 --> 00:21:03,960
Why are you here at this hour?

344
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:06,280
Here, have some tea. It's good tea.

345
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,839
I'll pass on the tea.

346
00:21:07,839 --> 00:21:09,039
Wu, where's your mom?

347
00:21:09,039 --> 00:21:10,859
My mom isn't in the shop.

348
00:21:10,859 --> 00:21:13,894
Fine. Then I'll wait for her here.

349
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,759
How about this? Don't just sit here waiting.

350
00:21:20,759 --> 00:21:23,000
I'll have Liu Nian give you a haircut.
Wait while he cuts it.

351
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:27,680
- Liu Nian, come here. Give Mr. Ma a haircut.
- Sure thing! Come on. Let me do it.

352
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:30,612
Do you think I even need a haircut?

353
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,200
How about a hair wash?

354
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,539
I washed it before I came.

355
00:21:35,539 --> 00:21:36,559
No need.

356
00:21:36,559 --> 00:21:39,039
Mr. Ma, come on. Just come to the shop anytime.

357
00:21:39,039 --> 00:21:41,773
Wash and cut are on the house.

358
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:44,480
Free things...

359
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,760
can't be taken forever.

360
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:47,440
They have to be paid back eventually.

361
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,447
Wu, don't you agree?

362
00:22:09,559 --> 00:22:11,079
Wait, Wu.

363
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:13,881
I think you missed a zero here.

364
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,026
As for the rest,

365
00:22:20,026 --> 00:22:21,400
we'll pay it back slowly.

366
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,200
That's not what your mom said last month.

367
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,224
She said once she saw off some "big shot,"

368
00:22:26,224 --> 00:22:29,061
she'd give us another 20,000 yuan.

369
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:32,079
Money is really tight lately.

370
00:22:32,079 --> 00:22:33,506
Could you give us

371
00:22:33,506 --> 00:22:35,193
a break?

372
00:22:35,193 --> 00:22:36,319
Tell you what.

373
00:22:36,319 --> 00:22:38,440
Give me another 2,700 yuan

374
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,279
to make it a round number.

375
00:22:40,279 --> 00:22:41,839
Then I can go back and report.

376
00:22:41,839 --> 00:22:44,524
Sir, Wu's bank account is already drained.

377
00:22:44,524 --> 00:22:48,247
Xuan Island has only 100 yuan left.
How are we supposed to pay you?

378
00:22:48,247 --> 00:22:50,039
Mr. Ma, give me two more days.

379
00:22:50,039 --> 00:22:52,759
Just two days.
I'll bring the money over to you then.

380
00:22:52,759 --> 00:22:55,160
How are you supposed to pay?

381
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:57,759
That's your problem,

382
00:22:57,759 --> 00:23:00,269
not mine.

383
00:23:00,842 --> 00:23:03,039
Wu, I'm not trying to make it hard for you.

384
00:23:03,039 --> 00:23:04,680
I'm just an employee too.

385
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:07,749
If I don't get the money today,

386
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:12,446
then I'll just stay here
and wait it out with you.

387
00:23:19,839 --> 00:23:21,876
I'll pay you.

388
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:25,640
This is none of your business. Stay out of it.

389
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:29,207
Pull up your payment QR code.

390
00:23:38,466 --> 00:23:40,280
Fine.

391
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:43,480
Wu, it's good to have a rich friend.

392
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,519
Pay the rest as soon as possible.

393
00:23:45,519 --> 00:23:47,504
If someone else comes next time,

394
00:23:47,504 --> 00:23:50,943
they might not be as easygoing as I am.

395
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,799
Where did you get that money?

396
00:23:57,799 --> 00:24:00,799
You didn't charge me
for fixing my computer last time.

397
00:24:00,799 --> 00:24:03,039
Consider this me paying you back.

398
00:24:03,039 --> 00:24:05,559
If you use all your money to pay for me,
what will you do?

399
00:24:05,559 --> 00:24:07,680
Live on thin air?

400
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:10,200
Well, you won't let me starve anyway.

401
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,960
That's true.

402
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,599
Money can always be earned back.

403
00:24:13,599 --> 00:24:16,232
We still have Xuan Island, don't we?

404
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:21,759
58 plus 30 plus 30 plus four 10s...

405
00:24:21,759 --> 00:24:23,000
Wait a second.

406
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:26,579
- 28 plus 30...
- 58.

407
00:24:26,579 --> 00:24:28,039
Plus 58...

408
00:24:28,039 --> 00:24:30,807
58 plus 30...

409
00:24:31,599 --> 00:24:33,039
3,659.

410
00:24:33,039 --> 00:24:35,565
3,659 yuan.

411
00:24:36,459 --> 00:24:39,319
Is that right? Stop calculating.

412
00:24:39,319 --> 00:24:40,800
Yeah, that's right.

413
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:43,799
Qing Ye, you did all that mental math?

414
00:24:43,799 --> 00:24:45,913
It wasn't that hard to calculate.

415
00:24:45,913 --> 00:24:47,000
Xing Wu,

416
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,720
from now on, someone can finally settle
Auntie Fang's accounts for you.

417
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,692
A modern-day female Zhuge Liang, Qing Ye.

418
00:24:52,692 --> 00:24:56,000
But I don't understand
how you've been keeping the books.

419
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,400
The numbers are way off.

420
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,873
What's wrong?

421
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:02,400
I arrived on the 10th of this month.

422
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,775
By the end of the month, that's 21 days.

423
00:25:04,775 --> 00:25:07,120
The net income was 3,150 yuan.

424
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:08,880
That's an average of 150 yuan a day.

425
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:11,359
Plus the 4,650 yuan

426
00:25:11,359 --> 00:25:13,039
from before I arrived.

427
00:25:13,039 --> 00:25:14,284
Last month, in July,

428
00:25:14,284 --> 00:25:15,799
it was the start of summer vacation.

429
00:25:15,799 --> 00:25:17,369
That should be the peak season.

430
00:25:17,369 --> 00:25:19,799
The actual income is definitely above average.

431
00:25:19,799 --> 00:25:21,920
Let's say it was over 5,000 yuan.

432
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:24,089
Liu Nian's wages,

433
00:25:24,089 --> 00:25:25,480
plus utilities

434
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,240
and other miscellaneous expenses,

435
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,559
total 3,600 yuan.

436
00:25:28,559 --> 00:25:30,800
Then last month's net income
should be over 1,000 yuan.

437
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:33,520
No way there's nothing left right now.

438
00:25:35,039 --> 00:25:36,979
Is that how it is?

439
00:25:36,979 --> 00:25:38,079
I think so.

440
00:25:38,079 --> 00:25:39,599
It was right at the start of the break.

441
00:25:39,599 --> 00:25:41,979
A lot of students came in.

442
00:25:41,979 --> 00:25:43,079
And think about it.

443
00:25:43,079 --> 00:25:44,759
In the past few months,

444
00:25:44,759 --> 00:25:46,079
Liu Nian's wages

445
00:25:46,079 --> 00:25:48,400
and all these miscellaneous expenses...

446
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:50,040
You didn't use Xuan Island's money.

447
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:52,920
You paid for them out of your own pocket.

448
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,519
So,

449
00:25:54,519 --> 00:25:56,593
where's the money?

450
00:25:56,593 --> 00:25:58,998
So, where's the money?

451
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:03,720
I'm back!

452
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:05,799
Oh, you're all here.

453
00:26:05,799 --> 00:26:07,840
Good. I just bought some seafood.

454
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:10,326
Let's eat together later.

455
00:26:12,559 --> 00:26:14,386
What's wrong?

456
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,920
The debt collectors just came.

457
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:22,110
Qing Ye had to pay 2,700 yuan
to get them to leave.

458
00:26:22,110 --> 00:26:24,298
Xuan Island can't even spare 200 yuan now,

459
00:26:24,298 --> 00:26:27,320
so where did the money go?

460
00:26:35,212 --> 00:26:36,359
What?

461
00:26:36,359 --> 00:26:39,359
So you're saying I spent
all of Xuan Island's money?

462
00:26:39,359 --> 00:26:40,839
Hello, Mom.

463
00:26:40,839 --> 00:26:43,379
Go home for dinner? Okay.

464
00:26:43,379 --> 00:26:44,491
I'm leaving, Auntie Fang.

465
00:26:44,491 --> 00:26:46,160
My mom asked me to help
serve dishes this morning.

466
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,859
I can still make it if I go now. Bye-bye!

467
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,286
I've been looking after Xuan Island
day and night.

468
00:27:03,286 --> 00:27:06,027
After taking care of the elderly,
I have to take care of the kids.

469
00:27:06,027 --> 00:27:07,680
Apart from shopping occasionally,

470
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:09,908
I don't have any other hobbies.

471
00:27:09,908 --> 00:27:11,160
What?

472
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,960
Are you auditing me now?

473
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,880
So it's all my fault?

474
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:16,909
No, no, Auntie.

475
00:27:16,909 --> 00:27:18,400
It's okay to like shopping.

476
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,960
Everyone has their hobbies.

477
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:21,640
It's just paying for happiness.

478
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,200
The most important thing is to be happy.

479
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,882
- Right?
- Exactly.

480
00:27:25,882 --> 00:27:28,480
That's exactly it.

481
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,319
It's just that today,

482
00:27:30,319 --> 00:27:32,079
after checking the books, we found

483
00:27:32,079 --> 00:27:35,079
that Xuan Island is actually profitable.

484
00:27:35,079 --> 00:27:37,000
We thought it wasn't making money anymore.

485
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:38,039
Not only is it profitable,

486
00:27:38,039 --> 00:27:39,440
but the money it makes

487
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:42,720
to support our family's expenses
is more than enough.

488
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:44,942
Look, this business

489
00:27:44,942 --> 00:27:47,595
isn't something
just anyone can run so well, Auntie.

490
00:27:47,595 --> 00:27:50,240
Even if my dad were here,
he wouldn't be as good as you.

491
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,440
Right?

492
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,960
See, I told you.

493
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:55,079
Running a business in a small town

494
00:27:55,079 --> 00:27:57,720
isn't something anyone can do.
There's a knack to it.

495
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:59,680
Not everyone can understand it.

496
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,440
I even bought seafood today.

497
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:02,880
Plus Xuan Island's daily expenses...

498
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:04,960
Don't they all have to come

499
00:28:04,960 --> 00:28:07,792
out of Xuan Island's accounts?

500
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,527
I'm not blaming you.

501
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,960
I never expected Xuan Island
to make much money anyway.

502
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,680
I didn't think it was still profitable.

503
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:18,000
Then...

504
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,799
the effort I put into Xuan Island

505
00:28:19,799 --> 00:28:22,400
wasn't in vain after all!

506
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,799
Ye.

507
00:28:23,799 --> 00:28:26,400
You're our family's savior.

508
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,960
From now on, just stay here
and make yourself at home.

509
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,279
I'm going to

510
00:28:30,279 --> 00:28:31,880
cook you something delicious.

511
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:33,210
Wait here.

512
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,559
Hello?

513
00:28:46,559 --> 00:28:49,000
How are things over in Hainan?

514
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,839
I want two more jobs.

515
00:28:50,839 --> 00:28:51,759
What?

516
00:28:51,759 --> 00:28:55,046
Paying debts and raising a cousin now?

517
00:28:55,759 --> 00:28:57,200
Canine sure has a big mouth.

518
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,279
Of course.

519
00:28:58,279 --> 00:28:59,559
My brother keeps me updated

520
00:28:59,559 --> 00:29:01,800
on your situation at all times.

521
00:29:02,472 --> 00:29:03,599
Wait for my call tonight.

522
00:29:03,599 --> 00:29:04,880
Okay.

523
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,326
Thanks.

524
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,873
Can I come in?

525
00:29:12,873 --> 00:29:13,880
Hold on a second.

526
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,766
I'm coming out.

527
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:23,559
What's up? Need something?

528
00:29:23,559 --> 00:29:27,480
I have something to discuss with you.

529
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:30,423
I also have a favor to ask of you.

530
00:29:30,423 --> 00:29:31,480
What is it?

531
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:33,000
You've seen how Xuan Island is.

532
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,000
Li Lan Fang's heart isn't in this at all.

533
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,160
She often takes money to play mahjong.

534
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,743
I'd like to ask for your help.

535
00:29:38,743 --> 00:29:39,759
At the end of each month,

536
00:29:39,759 --> 00:29:42,105
look over Xuan Island's books.

537
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,160
Actually,

538
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:46,400
that's exactly what I wanted to discuss.

539
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,640
But managing the books

540
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:49,160
treats the symptoms, not the cause.

541
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:51,638
It's better to fix it once and for all.

542
00:29:52,319 --> 00:29:54,392
What do you mean?

543
00:29:55,599 --> 00:29:58,160
Coming, coming!

544
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,839
The final dish:

545
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:02,240
Stir-fried squid.

546
00:30:02,893 --> 00:30:04,000
Not bad, huh?

547
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,160
All your favorites.

548
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,559
Come on, dig in!

549
00:30:06,559 --> 00:30:08,160
Dig in.

550
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:09,319
Auntie, Grandma,

551
00:30:09,319 --> 00:30:10,480
I have something to tell you.

552
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:11,160
Go ahead.

553
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,680
I want to revitalize

554
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:14,592
Xuan Island's business.

555
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,880
You've already covered the debt.

556
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:22,519
You don't need to waste your time on this.

557
00:30:22,519 --> 00:30:25,480
I don't think it's a waste of time.

558
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:28,240
Isn't my dream to become rich?

559
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:29,640
Revitalizing Xuan Island

560
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:32,519
is one small step toward realizing that dream.

561
00:30:32,519 --> 00:30:36,240
Ye, I know you mean well.

562
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,680
But running a business

563
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,720
isn't like going to school.

564
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,039
It's not that simple.

565
00:30:41,039 --> 00:30:43,400
Besides, are you afraid I can't compete

566
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:46,279
with the other three barbershops?

567
00:30:46,279 --> 00:30:47,279
No, Auntie.

568
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:49,519
Just think of it as supporting my dream.

569
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:50,920
Grandma supports you.

570
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,880
Thank you, Grandma.

571
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:54,640
Don't get too ahead of yourself.

572
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:56,400
Who's getting ahead of themselves?

573
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:59,759
I'm being completely sincere.

574
00:30:59,759 --> 00:31:01,599
The hairtail fish can bear witness.

575
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:03,279
Wait until I finish a complete proposal.

576
00:31:03,279 --> 00:31:06,479
Look it over, then decide whether to do it.

577
00:31:06,479 --> 00:31:09,040
Fine. We'll see then.

578
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,240
Low expectations

579
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:13,960
often lead to unexpected surprises.

580
00:31:16,039 --> 00:31:18,185
Alright, alright.

581
00:31:18,185 --> 00:31:19,279
A "complete proposal," huh?

582
00:31:19,279 --> 00:31:21,819
Just eat more for now.

583
00:31:43,599 --> 00:31:45,458
Wu.

584
00:31:46,079 --> 00:31:47,519
This is the work that piled up

585
00:31:47,519 --> 00:31:49,520
while you were away.

586
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:51,599
Give it to me.

587
00:31:51,599 --> 00:31:53,919
I'll fix them gradually.

588
00:32:01,166 --> 00:32:02,279
Liu Nian,

589
00:32:02,279 --> 00:32:03,359
let me ask you something.

590
00:32:03,359 --> 00:32:05,599
We mostly do medium-short hair,

591
00:32:05,599 --> 00:32:08,053
with perms and dyes, right?

592
00:32:08,053 --> 00:32:09,160
That's right.

593
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,720
The main revenue comes from

594
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,880
female customers aged 35 and up.

595
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:15,039
If you and Auntie both work on it,

596
00:32:15,039 --> 00:32:16,839
how many can you do in a day?

597
00:32:16,839 --> 00:32:18,319
Let me think...

598
00:32:18,319 --> 00:32:21,279
When business was good a few years ago,

599
00:32:21,279 --> 00:32:23,579
about 15 or so.

600
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:47,079
I don't believe in bad luck.

601
00:32:47,079 --> 00:32:50,520
Today, I'm definitely going to
win a big hand at mahjong.

602
00:32:52,039 --> 00:32:54,480
What are those two doing?

603
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:56,759
Dreaming of getting rich.

604
00:32:56,759 --> 00:32:57,880
Auntie.

605
00:32:57,880 --> 00:33:00,599
It looks quite formal.

606
00:33:00,599 --> 00:33:02,079
Let's put in some effort too.

607
00:33:02,079 --> 00:33:04,239
Let's go.

608
00:33:05,519 --> 00:33:06,720
What do you think?

609
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:09,079
This proposal is very detailed.

610
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,472
But it's just a plan.

611
00:33:11,472 --> 00:33:12,559
How do we implement it?

612
00:33:12,559 --> 00:33:14,539
Why wouldn't we be able to?

613
00:33:14,539 --> 00:33:15,799
I've visited

614
00:33:15,799 --> 00:33:17,880
all three competing barbershops.

615
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,000
I noticed one of them,

616
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,440
called Fashion Pioneer,

617
00:33:20,440 --> 00:33:22,298
is doing the best.

618
00:33:22,298 --> 00:33:23,440
I observed for a while.

619
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,519
Its average daily customer flow is

620
00:33:25,519 --> 00:33:27,079
20 to 30 people.

621
00:33:27,079 --> 00:33:28,839
Like Xuan Island, it also has

622
00:33:28,839 --> 00:33:31,359
two employees in total, including the owner.

623
00:33:31,359 --> 00:33:33,079
Men's cuts are 15 yuan.

624
00:33:33,079 --> 00:33:34,400
Women's cuts are 25 yuan.

625
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,599
Perms and dyes

626
00:33:35,599 --> 00:33:37,680
are also between 150 and 200 yuan.

627
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,680
Its pricing is definitely
lower than Xuan Island's.

628
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,079
As for its customer base,

629
00:33:41,079 --> 00:33:42,200
it's mostly regulars.

630
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,160
Plus, the age range is on the older side.

631
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:44,920
Right.

632
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,480
So compared to it,

633
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:48,483
Xuan Island has no price advantage.

634
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,480
No advantage at all.

635
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:54,000
Even with the customer base,
we have no advantage.

636
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,839
But we can attract

637
00:33:55,839 --> 00:33:57,000
younger customers later.

638
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,359
But the people you're talking about

639
00:33:58,359 --> 00:34:00,240
don't usually get their hair done
in Zhazhating.

640
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:02,603
They'd rather go to the city or the county.

641
00:34:03,839 --> 00:34:05,359
That's why

642
00:34:05,359 --> 00:34:06,599
we need to make Xuan Island

643
00:34:06,599 --> 00:34:08,599
their first choice.

644
00:34:08,599 --> 00:34:10,760
That's how we increase revenue.

645
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,565
How so?

646
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:14,920
I've thought it through.

647
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,440
I'm going to transform Xuan Island.

648
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,639
If there's no demand,

649
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:19,159
we create it.

650
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:20,360
Launch new hairstyles

651
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,719
and use new techniques

652
00:34:21,719 --> 00:34:22,983
to attract new customers.

653
00:34:22,983 --> 00:34:24,079
Increase our visibility.

654
00:34:24,079 --> 00:34:26,677
Then take some stylized promotional photos.

655
00:34:26,677 --> 00:34:27,679
Hand out flyers

656
00:34:27,679 --> 00:34:29,773
to get Xuan Island's name out there.

657
00:34:29,773 --> 00:34:32,639
Then get them to buy memberships
to retain those customers.

658
00:34:32,639 --> 00:34:33,760
What era are we in?

659
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:35,760
Who still hands out flyers?

660
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,519
Yeah, everyone is on their phones now.

661
00:34:37,519 --> 00:34:39,919
But like they say,
Zhazhating is a tight-knit community.

662
00:34:39,919 --> 00:34:40,760
So handing out flyers

663
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,159
is the most direct and effective way

664
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,280
to acquire new customers.

665
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:45,440
The key is that these flyers

666
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:46,559
must be made to be

667
00:34:46,559 --> 00:34:49,439
targeted, sophisticated, and appealing.

668
00:34:51,985 --> 00:34:53,000
I was thinking...

669
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,239
if Xuan Island's business

670
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:56,880
really picks up,

671
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,840
then you won't have to
work so many extra jobs

672
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:01,199
and be so tired because of me.

673
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,599
But you're only

674
00:35:07,599 --> 00:35:10,440
part of the reason.

675
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:12,519
Didn't you say

676
00:35:12,519 --> 00:35:14,239
you treat me like family?

677
00:35:14,239 --> 00:35:16,159
I want to treat this place as home too,

678
00:35:16,159 --> 00:35:19,000
and help lighten your burden.

679
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,079
Just...

680
00:35:21,079 --> 00:35:22,599
trust me with Xuan Island.

681
00:35:22,599 --> 00:35:24,473
I'm confident.

682
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:31,400
Why are you looking at me?

683
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:33,000
So, have you decided?

684
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:35,186
Are we doing this or not?

685
00:35:37,320 --> 00:35:38,679
Let's give it a try then.

686
00:35:38,679 --> 00:35:41,159
Regardless of the outcome.

687
00:35:41,159 --> 00:35:42,985
Okay.

688
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:48,599
These all look so good.

689
00:35:48,599 --> 00:35:50,243
I downloaded these

690
00:35:50,243 --> 00:35:52,800
from the social media of a stylist
I know in Beijing.

691
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:53,559
Not bad, right?

692
00:35:53,559 --> 00:35:55,039
Not bad.

693
00:35:55,039 --> 00:35:57,680
This hairstyle looks quite hard to do.

694
00:36:04,239 --> 00:36:07,079
The coffee you make is the best.

695
00:36:07,079 --> 00:36:08,939
Try the snacks I made too.

696
00:36:08,939 --> 00:36:10,039
You made them yourself?

697
00:36:10,039 --> 00:36:10,960
Yes, I made them myself.

698
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,159
- What are these?
- Try one.

699
00:36:12,159 --> 00:36:13,400
Is this mung bean cake?

700
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:15,240
Yes, try it.

701
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,679
You know, Ye...

702
00:37:22,679 --> 00:37:24,400
she's really something.

703
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:25,960
She came here just to stay,

704
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:28,159
but now she's running the place.

705
00:37:28,159 --> 00:37:29,920
Do you know what note she left me?

706
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:34,159
"You're twice as charming
when you don't play mahjong."

707
00:37:34,159 --> 00:37:35,920
And a few days ago,

708
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,639
the note she left me then said,

709
00:37:37,639 --> 00:37:39,639
"Auntie, you're the best

710
00:37:39,639 --> 00:37:41,360
boss lady in the world."

711
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,519
What do you call that?

712
00:37:42,519 --> 00:37:44,159
Kids these days really know such stuff.

713
00:37:44,159 --> 00:37:46,760
It's called the carrot and the stick.

714
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:49,360
Don't underestimate this girl.
She's really got what it takes.

715
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:51,660
That bookkeeping ledger of hers

716
00:37:51,660 --> 00:37:52,719
is actually quite useful.

717
00:37:52,719 --> 00:37:53,400
Is it?

718
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,760
Hu is using it for us now, too.

719
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:57,360
It really is quite convenient.

720
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,599
Maybe this girl really can get your Xuan Island

721
00:37:59,599 --> 00:38:01,039
back on its feet.

722
00:38:01,039 --> 00:38:03,360
They're just a bunch of kids.

723
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:04,880
I'm not so sure.

724
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:06,159
You never know.

725
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:07,519
Don't forget, back then,

726
00:38:07,519 --> 00:38:08,760
you only trained for two months

727
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:10,039
before you opened Xuan Island.

728
00:38:10,039 --> 00:38:11,360
And how old was I

729
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,320
when I took over my mom's mahjong parlor?

730
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,920
And you, Xi Xi,

731
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,159
right after high school,

732
00:38:16,159 --> 00:38:18,239
you started dating Hu's dad.

733
00:38:18,239 --> 00:38:19,880
What are you two talking about?

734
00:38:19,880 --> 00:38:21,360
I was eighteen or nineteen then.

735
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:22,719
So what if I was dating? So what?

736
00:38:22,719 --> 00:38:24,000
We were so young back then.

737
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:24,760
True.

738
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:25,840
- Exactly.
- Ah, youth...

739
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,639
Now our kids are eighteen or nineteen.

740
00:38:27,639 --> 00:38:30,519
Where did our youth go?

741
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:36,599
♪ My youth, like a little bird ♪

742
00:38:36,599 --> 00:38:39,160
♪ has flown away never to return ♪

743
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:42,960
♪ My youth, like a little bird ♪

744
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:45,960
♪ has flown away never to return ♪

745
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:48,399
Who hasn't had their youth?

746
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:51,019
Let's play mahjong.

747
00:38:51,019 --> 00:38:52,159
Just one round.

748
00:38:52,159 --> 00:38:54,360
Only one round.

749
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:56,692
That doesn't sound like you.

750
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:04,145
Xing Wu.

751
00:39:04,145 --> 00:39:05,320
I've finished revising the plan.

752
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:06,529
Do you want to see it?

753
00:39:06,529 --> 00:39:07,400
No need.

754
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,360
Then we'll follow the plan tomorrow.

755
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:10,760
Okay.

756
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,880
But we don't have any models.

757
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,840
Yes, we do. They're right here.

758
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,726
Who?

759
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:22,840
Are you sure?

760
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:24,440
Don't believe me?

761
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:26,440
Let's make a bet then.

762
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,039
Fine. You're on.

763
00:39:28,039 --> 00:39:28,800
North Wind.

764
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:29,760
Me?

765
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:30,679
Us?

766
00:39:30,679 --> 00:39:32,599
Models?

767
00:39:35,719 --> 00:39:37,105
Ye,

768
00:39:37,105 --> 00:39:39,679
you flatter us too much.

769
00:39:39,679 --> 00:39:40,599
Let me tell you,

770
00:39:40,599 --> 00:39:41,639
your auntie here...

771
00:39:41,639 --> 00:39:44,039
Back in younger days,
I might have been a beauty.

772
00:39:44,039 --> 00:39:45,360
But at our age now,

773
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:47,679
if you make us stand on a stage
and wiggle around,

774
00:39:47,679 --> 00:39:49,079
it would be so embarrassing.

775
00:39:49,079 --> 00:39:50,360
Exactly, Qing Ye.

776
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:51,719
At our age,

777
00:39:51,719 --> 00:39:53,559
we'll be grandmas in a few years.

778
00:39:53,559 --> 00:39:54,679
If word gets out,

779
00:39:54,679 --> 00:39:55,880
we'll be a laughingstock.

780
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:57,760
I won't laugh. I'd love to see it. I'd love it.

781
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,000
What's it to you?

782
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:01,239
When women are talking,
why do you keep interrupting?

783
00:40:01,239 --> 00:40:03,280
What you're thinking of are runway models.

784
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:04,719
Models for a fashion show.

785
00:40:04,719 --> 00:40:07,559
What I want you to be are print models.

786
00:40:07,559 --> 00:40:09,639
Whether it's print or whatever,

787
00:40:09,639 --> 00:40:12,920
modelling is for young girls.

788
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:14,599
We're all mothers now.

789
00:40:14,599 --> 00:40:15,920
It's too embarrassing.

790
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:17,840
No, not at all.

791
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:20,800
Every age has its own kind of beauty.

792
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:23,879
Qing Ye, what do you need models for?

793
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:26,199
To take promo photos for Xuan Island.

794
00:40:26,199 --> 00:40:27,599
Look,

795
00:40:27,599 --> 00:40:29,480
this is my flyer.

796
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,519
In the spaces besides the text,

797
00:40:31,519 --> 00:40:32,679
right here, here, and here.

798
00:40:32,679 --> 00:40:34,360
I want to put photos of real people.

799
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:35,678
Photos of real people?

800
00:40:35,678 --> 00:40:38,400
Then how do you plan to promote it?

801
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:39,840
Think about it, Auntie.

802
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,480
For Xuan Island

803
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:42,880
to have good business,

804
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,039
don't we need to

805
00:40:44,039 --> 00:40:45,360
expand our customer base?

806
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:46,519
How do we expand it?

807
00:40:46,519 --> 00:40:48,159
We need to increase brand awareness.

808
00:40:48,159 --> 00:40:49,880
And how do we do that?

809
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:52,683
We must step up our publicity efforts.

810
00:40:52,683 --> 00:40:53,519
Look.

811
00:40:53,519 --> 00:40:55,323
Xuan Island's main customer base

812
00:40:55,323 --> 00:40:57,800
is women aged between 35 and 55.

813
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,720
That's exactly your age range.

814
00:41:01,459 --> 00:41:02,480
Wait, Qing Ye.

815
00:41:02,480 --> 00:41:05,199
All this talk about publicity
and customer bases...

816
00:41:05,199 --> 00:41:06,960
We don't really understand it.

817
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:09,199
Exactly. Do we even need promotion?

818
00:41:09,199 --> 00:41:11,283
Who doesn't know about Fang's skills?

819
00:41:11,283 --> 00:41:13,320
The perms she does
don't lose their curls for half a year.

820
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:14,440
That's right.

821
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,320
Exactly.

822
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,480
Our technique is solid.

823
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:18,280
That's our core competitiveness.

824
00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:20,039
We need to let people know that.

825
00:41:20,039 --> 00:41:21,398
So, the three of you

826
00:41:21,398 --> 00:41:23,519
will be the spokeswomen for Xuan Island.

827
00:41:23,519 --> 00:41:25,956
Just show off your beautiful selves.

828
00:41:25,956 --> 00:41:27,380
When people see how beautiful you are,

829
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:30,840
naturally, more people
will come to Xuan Island.

830
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,880
Isn't this the celebrity effect?

831
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:33,880
Your niece

832
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:36,920
is treating you three like stars.

833
